                        "etapes": [
                            {
                                "titre": "•Herbal tea is (obviously) chock full of Mother Earth's finest gifts, so you know replacing some of your product with tea will add some healthy ingredients *if you brew it & use liquid form, just keep an eye (& nose) out for spoilage•Add Cocoa Butter to extra thick lotion -& a scented oil and you got body butter",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "•Peppermint Oil is a wonderful \"pick-me-up\" , invigorating scent & can be helpful to the scalp & tired/achy feet",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "•Wintergreen, Eucalyptus oil can turn your lotion into a muscle rub/cream •Did you know Epsom Salt dissolved in water is called Magnesium Oil? It works wonders on aches & pains and soaks in really fast; include some of that in thickened cream with wintergreen and/or eucalyptus oils -& look out pain! (the lotion helps with the powdery residue Epsom salts can leave behind) •the *HEATED* oils (magnesium-water with wintergreen/eucalyptus) soaked in a cloth or towel is an awesome wrap too!•*Be sure to use caution with mint and vapor \"radiata\" oils; watch for skin burning",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "•Walnut shells (or practically any nut shells you may have) crunched up make a scrub",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "•Oats as well -great for face masks too!•Don't forget the dry tea (loose leaves or tea bag) just add some grounds in",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "•Thicken your conditioner & add olive oil for a deep treatment (especially for dry/split-ends)",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "•note, adding essential/fragrance oils (even coconut oil) to shampoos and conditioner reacts -but not bad- it just thins it out considerably, so think 'Splash' ~possibly after shave..",
